  <span id="freeText13170490580837920388" style="display:none">Full review: <a target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow" href="https://bookpeopleteens.wordpress.com/2020/08/13/review-vampires-never-get-old/">https://bookpeopleteens.wordpress.com...</a><br /><br /><i>“When you leave this place, step out into late evening quiet for the first time, reborn. Take in the glittering, crumbling streets around you. Look into the ink-black night. It’s dark. And full of diamonds. And you, dear one, are made of stardust.”</i> from "A Guidebook to the Newly Sired Desi Vampire" by <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/author/show/8345582.Samira_Ahmed" title="Samira Ahmed" rel="nofollow noopener">Samira Ahmed</a><br /><br />Overall, <i>Vampires Never Get Old</i> has the biggest sucker punch of a titular pun I’ve ever read and nearly a dozen modern blood-sucking tales featuring queer, disabled, and racially diverse teens biting and being bitten. It’s a lot of silliness mixed with a whole lot of heart because you can tell that every contributor shares the one thing most YA readers still secretly possess: an embarrassingly deep love of vampires. <b>Rating: four stakes to the heart/five</b></span>
