  <span id="freeText13597005996506377643" style="display:none">Vampires Never Get Old is a collection of eleven short stories by a diverse cast of famous YA authors. Like all anthologies that I read before, there were stories that I liked more than others. One of my favorites was<br />Mirrors, Windows &amp; Selfies by Mark Oshiro. Unfortunately there were more that I found a bit boring and chessy for my taste. Maybe I'm not the right audience for this anthology but I'm sure a lot of people will love it.<br />3.5 stars<br />The Arc of this book was provided by Macmillan Children's Publishing Group via Netgalley in exchange for an honest review</span>
